	(text "λ = c/f = 3×10⁸ / 924×10⁶ = 324.7 mm\n\nThe J-pole has two sections:\nRadiating element (half wave):\nL_radiator = λ/2 × VF = 162.3 × 0.95 = 154.2 mm\nMatching stub (quarter wave):\nL_stub = λ/4 × VF = 81.2 × 0.95 = 77.1 mm\n\nFeed point gap between stub and radiator:\nApproximately 3 to 5 mm - this is where your SMA connects and where your tuning trimming traces go.\nTrace width for the antenna elements on FR4 1.6mm:\nFor a 50 Ω microstrip on FR4 1.6mm with εr = 4.4:\nW = approximately 3.0 mm"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
